[src:ruby/core-array-p03] With a block given, calls the block with each element of `self`; removes each element for which the block returns a truthy value.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] With a block given, calls the block with each repeated combination of length `size` of the elements of `self`; each combination is an array; returns `self`.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] The order of the combinations is indeterminate.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] If a positive integer argument `size` is given, calls the block with each `size`-tuple repeated combination of the elements of `self`.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] The number of combinations is `(size+1)(size+2)/2`.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] If `size` is zero, calls the block once with an empty array.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] With a block given, calls the block with each repeated permutation of length `size` of the elements of `self`; each permutation is an array; returns `self`.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] The order of the permutations is indeterminate.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] If a positive integer argument `size` is given, calls the block with each `size`-tuple repeated permutation of the elements of `self`.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] The number of permutations is `self.size**size`.
[src:ruby/core-array-p03] When no block given, returns a new `Enumerator`.
