[src:ruby/enumerable-p02] This method split chunks between *elt_before* and *elt_after* where the block returns `false`.
[src:ruby/enumerable-p02] The block is called the length of the receiver enumerator minus one.
[src:ruby/enumerable-p02] The result enumerator yields the chunked elements as an array.
[src:ruby/enumerable-p02] Other methods of the `Enumerator` class and `Enumerable` module, such as `to_a`, `map`, etc., are also usable.
[src:ruby/enumerable-p02] `Enumerable#slice_when` does the same, except splitting when the block returns `true` instead of `false`.
[src:ruby/enumerable-p02] Returns an array of objects returned by the block.
